[dev]Picking up items||&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Hover the mouse cursor over an this sword, and click LMB when it turns to a glove.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;The item will land in Geralt's hand or inventory.
[dev]Interacting with characters||&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;There are red vitality indicators under hostile characters. To attack this kind of character, click on it once with LMB. &#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Characters with green vitality indicators are your friends. Click on them once to start a conversation (works only when not in combat).
[dev]Combat basics||You've attacked an enemy. Remember to not to click when Geralt is performing an attack. To continue attacking, click on your opponent only, when orange sword trail is visible, and when the mouse cursor turns into flaming sword (only in easy difficulty level). &#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Geralt is always performing a whirl animation, and a whirl sound is played, when it's perfect time to click.
[dev]Kontynuacja ataku||You've clicked to fast, and Geralt broke the attack. Remeber to click only when Geralt is performing the whirl animation and orange sword trail is visible.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;The whirl sound is also helpful to find the exact moment. 
[dev]Hero movement basics||To rotate the camera, bring the cursor nearer a screen edge. You can also click and hold the MMB, and move the mouse. &#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;If you click on ground with LMB, Geralt will go to chosen destination. When you click and hold the LMB, Geralt will move in the direction of the cursor.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;The camera works in three modes, you can switch them, by pressing: , , on your keyboard.
[dev]Map||There is a minimap in the right - upper corner of the screen. Red dot marks the place you should go to, to complete your current task. If this place is very distant, a red arrow will point you the direction to that place.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Press the key, or click on the map icon to bring up the location map panel.
[dev] Using objects and combat mode || To open the gate you need to use a winch, clicking LMB on it. But first you need to kill all the enemies, because you can't use objects in the combat mode. &#x0D;&#x0A;Whenever there are enemies around, Combat Mode activates. In combat mode you can attack your enemies and cast Signs. You cannot use objects, doors, pick up items, talk to friendly characters and leave your current area.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;In combat mode you cannot use majority of the items and objects you encounter. Special objects which can be used during boss fights are exceptions.&#x0D;&#x0A;Press Alt to highlight all the usable items in your vicinity.
[dev] Gifts||Doubleclick LMB on the elixir, to give it to Triss. &#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;If you're looking for some information or you want to make a friend with somebody, it's good to give a little present. It will also help you flirt with women. Wrong gift can offend your interlocutor.
[dev]Combat styles: fast style||&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;From now on you can use fast style to defend opponents. Switch the style by clicking on a button on the left of the screen and strike this opponent. It's the only way you can defeat him. &#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Use fast style when fighting with agile opponenrs. Strikes in this style are more accurate, and hard to dodge. Fast style deals less damage than the stronge one. You can also switch to this style by pressing .
Combat styles: fast style||&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Use the fast style, when fighting with an agile opponent. He will not be able to dodge your strikes.
Combat styles: strong style||&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;This opponent is muscular, and tough. Use the strong style to defeat him.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Use the strong style when fighting with big, muscular or armored opponents. This style deals great damage, and pierces armor. It's not effective against agile villians, because it's not that accurate. You can switch to strong style also by pressing .
[dev]Combat styles: strong style||&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Use the strong style when fighting with muscular or armored opponents. &#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;You will deal more damage, and defeat the opponent faster.
Combat styles: switching styles||One of this opponents is agile, the other - muscular. Defeat them both by switching combat styles.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;It's easier to change a combat style, when in active pause. You can enter active pause by pressing SPACJÄ˜.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;In the Options panel you can define your own keyboard shortcuts to choose combat styles.
Using elixirs||You received two elixirs. Drink Thunder. Open Equipment screen, find the elixir icon and press RMB. This way you can use a lot of items you own.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;You can put an elixir in the special quickslots. Grab its icon with LMB and drag it to the highlighted slot. Elixir will be shown in the middle left of the screen and you'll be able to using any time pressing LMB.
Elixirs effects||Icons of effects currently affecting Geralt appear in the ring encircling your medallion. Hover mouse cursor over an icon to get more information about the effect.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Every elixir you dring rises toxicity level. If green bar fills up, Geralt loses half of his vitality points. If the witcher drinks another elixir, toxicity kills him.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;There are elixirs with short-term duration (around 10 - 30 minutes) and long-term duration (about 8 hours).
Combat styles: Group style||You have encountered a group of weak opponents. Choose group style to defeat them quickly.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Group style is effective only against a group of weak opponents. You have drunk witcher's elixir, so this group is not a challenge to you. Group style attacks wound all the opponents in your sword distance. Damage you deal is greater when you're fighting with more enemies. You can enable group style pressing .
Escape from combat||To jump away from the opponents, click twice LMP on the ground. The witcher will jump in that direction and escapes from combat.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Jumping away can be an effective tactics during fights with a few enemies as well as with one stronger enemy.
Circles of Elements||In the stone circles Geralt can learn one of the witchers' signs. Look for Circles of Elements to acquire new signs.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;When you use the stone obelisk already knowing the sign you'll get additional temporary enhancement of that sign's power.
Using signs||You can destroy the obstacle using sign of Aard. To cast a sign click RMB on the target. Every usage of the sign will lower Geralt's endurance level represented by yellow bar.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Sign of Aard knocks your opponents down allowing you to perform coup de grace. Aard cast at the obstacle destroys it. &#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Too low endurance level disallows you to use signs.
Rest||You can enter the rest mode choosing Rest icon in the conversation with some characters.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;During rest you can meditate to accelerate time flow, recover vitality level and bring toxicity level back to normal.
Campfires||Click on the burning campfire to enter the rest mode.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;You can meditate at the burning campfires. Campfire ignites if you have got flint in your inventory. Otherwise you can cast Igni sign to ignite it.
Diary||Open the diary clicking on its icon to check your quest progress or find information you need.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Pulsating icon means that you've got new information. Click the icon to read it.
[dev] Alchemy basics||&#x0D;&#x0A;Now you can prepare elixirs alone in the rest mode.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Every elixir consists of base and a mixture of colourful substances. Use alcohol as a base for your elixirs and dissolve substances in it. Your elixir will be brewed right if the mixture of substances will satisfy elixir's recipe.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Recipes of known elixirs you can find in your diary in Alchemy tab. You can learn new recipes from books or characters you meet. You can also experiment.
[dev] Skinning monsters||Click on the dead monster's body to extract the alchemical components from it. Move the component to your inventory.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;From each monster you can extract base component and advanced component. They differ in alchemical substances. To be able to find an advanced component, you need to have knowledge about the monster. You can learn it from books or people you meet.
[dev] Elixir preparation||To brew an elixir you need to enter the rest mode and turn the Alchemy screen on. If you've got all the components, the base and elixir's recipe, click the recipe to create the elixir. &#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;You can also try to experiment and create elixir on your own. Take a base and put it in hilighted slot. Similarly move all the components. Observe how the substances in the elixir change. If you're sure your elixir is ready, press Mix button.
[dev] Character development||To develop your character, choose an ability tree, then click on the ability you want to buy. You can read its description if you select it with mouse.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;There are 3 sorts of development points called Talents. They correspond to 3 types of skills: bronze, silver and gold. You'll get first Silver Talents at 15 character level, and gold - at 34 character level. You can get Talents also when you drink powerful mutagens elixirs.
[dev] Witcher's medallion||If you set your medallion to detect monsters, it alerts you on any monsters in your vicinity. If you set it to detect magic, it vibrates when you are near any Places of Power, making finding them easier.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Vibration is stronger when danger or magic is closer. Observe your medallion's behavior, because it can warn you before otherwise surprising attack.
[dev] Sequences ||&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;If you buy next level of the combat style, you get another stroke in the attack sequence.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Remember that when you are attacking an enemy you've got to click LMB only when you see the orange trail on your sword. If you click too early, Geralt breaks the attack sequence and does not perform additional stroke.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;You can buy additional effects to every additional stroke.
[dev] Vitality||Wounds you get are lowering vitality level. If red vitality bar falls to zero, Geralt dies.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Ashy picture and heartbeat sound alarm you about low vitality level.
[dev] Drinking alcohol||&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;If you drink too much alcohol, the picture gets blurry and Geralt's efficiency in combat lowers.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Negative effects last a few hours and vanish after short meditation. Eating some food can shorten the negative effect of the alcohol. If you overdose the alcohol, you can lose consciousness and during combat it equals death.
[dev] Herbalism||Now you can gather herbs to collect alchemical components. Click on the applicable plant to get the component.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;To be able to collect herbs you need to have a specific knowledge about that herb. You can learn it from books or people you meet.
[dev] New signs||Now you can use new witcher's sign. When you learn a new sign, its ability tree appears in character development panel.&#x0D;&#x0A;An icon of your new sign appears on the lower left side of the screen. You can switch between different signs clicking LMB on their icons. In the Options screen you can define keyboard shortcuts to specific signs.
[dev] Silver witcher's sword||A silver sword is very effective against monsters. Try to use it always when you combat unnatural creatures.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Some monsters are affected only by a silver sword. The knowledge of steel sword combat has no effect on your abilities in the silver sword. Expand your abilities in both sword types to be fully effective in fights with humans as well as with monsters.&#x0D;&#x0A;
[dev] Annoucements||Notice the announcements posted on message boards. They activate some side quests.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Open the equipment panel and read the announcement clicking LMB on it to get to know more about its details and start solving the task.&#x0D;&#x0A;
[dev] Fistfight||Yellow vitality marker depicts characters you can fight with bare hands. To attack such a character click LMB on its silhouette. Click once more when a cursor turns to a flaming fist to activate an attack sequence.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;You can buy some abilities from the Dexterity and Strength trees to be more effective in fist fighting.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Fighting in the inns you can earn some money.
[dev] Attack sequence (2) ||Try to observe Geralt carefully. At the end of his stroke he performs distinctive sword whirl and the edge leaves flaming trail. It is just an appropriate moment to click on the enemy again.
[dev] Attack sequence (3) ||If you click too early you kick Geralt out of the rhythm. You need to click just when you notice the orange sword trail and distinctive whirl, hear special sound and the cursor changes to the flaming sword. A cursor shall be positioned over the enemy.
[dev] Dice poker ||You can earn little money playing dice. Choose the bet and throw dice. You can bid and choose dice to throw again. Player who acquires better result wins.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;Some people require you to play a few rounds. It means that you won't be able to leave the table with your money after one round.
[dev] Keyboard control ||Use following keys to control your character: , , , . Rotate camera with the mouse. Press LMB to perform an action on the object highlighted on the center of the screen.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;If you press any of the directional keys during combat twice, Geralt jumps. Press to show the cursor and select a Sign or a combat style using your mouse.&#x0D;&#x0A;&#x0D;&#x0A;You can switch camera to isometric view pressing , to point&amp;click mode using , and go back to the TPP mode pressing .
